TEXT(beginproblem());

############################################################
# PG Setup Code
############################################################
$p = randomPerson();
$b = random(32,37);
$d = random(2,2.5,0.1);
$sol = (60 - $b)/$d;
$start = NumberWithUnits($b, 'min');
$distance = NumberWithUnits($d, 'mi');
$rate = NumberWithUnits($sol, 'min/mi');
Context("Interval");
Context()->flags->set(ignoreEndpointTypes => 1);
$interval = OneOf(Interval("(0,$sol)"), Interval("(-inf,$sol)"));
Context("LinearRelation")->variables->are(x => 'Real');
Context()->noreduce('(-x)-y', '(-x)+y');
$relation = Formula("$b+x*$d < 60");

############################################################
# Body
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML
[$p] is a runner, and set out this morning on a jog with a goal to reach a nearby summit and return home in under one hour. [$p->They] jogged a steady uphill path to the top of the nearby summit, and it took [$start] to get there. Now jogging home, [$p->they] will run a distance of [$distance]. What will [$p->their] rate (in minutes per mile) need to be in order to make the goal of returning home in under 60 minutes?

END_PGML

############################################################
# Scaffold
############################################################
Scaffold::Begin(numbered => 1,is_open => "correct_or_first_incorrect",can_open => always,);

############################################################
# Section
############################################################
Section::Begin("");

BEGIN_PGML
Write an inequality to represent this situation, using [`x`] to represent [$p]'s jogging rate in minutes per mile.

[_]{$relation}{16}

END_PGML

Section::End();

############################################################
# Section
############################################################
Section::Begin("");

BEGIN_PGML
Solve this inequality. [$p]'s jogging rate needs to beat what rate?

[_]{$rate}{16}

END_PGML

Section::End();

############################################################
# Section
############################################################
Section::Begin("");

BEGIN_PGML
Use interval notation to express what [$p]'s jogging rate (in minutes per mile) might be.

[_]{$interval}{16}

END_PGML

Section::End();

Scaffold::End();

